DESCRIPTION — MALE: Body length 1.8-2.9 mm . Head and mesosoma dark castaneous; metasoma castaneous. Head (Figure 24). Mandible with four apical teeth. Clypeus with median lobe subtrapezoidal; median tooth subangulate; median carina distinctly incomplete apically and straight in profile. Frons strongly coriaceous. Mesosoma. Pronotal disc with anterior margin carinate, strongly coriaceous. Metapectal-propodeal complex with lateral and posterior areas partly carinate. Metasoma (Figure 120). Tergal process with deep, subcircular and sublateral pair of depression, 0.48 x as long as tergite II, diverging posterad, with long and thin setae on lateral area, inner margin of depression slightly higher

Hypopygium (Figure 213) with median stalk evenly narrow, 1.3 x as long as hypopygial plate; lateral stalk triangular; posterior margin straight or nearly so and pair of medians excavations. Genitalia (Figures 356-357). Aedeagal dorsal body with apex lower than parameral apex, evenly narrow. Aedeagal ventral ramus with apex higher than aedeagal dorsal body apex, slightly bifurcated on apical region; apical region subangled and smooth. Genital ring produced, each half convex in dorsal view.

ETYMOLOGY — The noun in apposition
gamtri
means eucalyptus tree in Tok Pisin.
